# define functions
def percentageNaN(ser):
    boolnotNaN = np.isfinite(ser)
    return 1-np.sum(boolnotNaN)/len(ser)

def correlation(ser1,ser2):
    boolnotNaN=np.isfinite(ser1)&np.isfinite(ser2)
    return np.corrcoef(ser1[boolnotNaN],ser2[boolnotNaN])[0,1]

def R2(y_true, y_fit):
    R2 = 1 - np.sum((y_true - y_fit)**2) / np.sum(y_true**2)
    return R2

def normalize(series):
    return (series-series.mean(axis=0))/series.std(axis=0)

def sliding_window(df, min_train_size, horizon):
    '''
    sliding window generator
    '''
    train = list(set(df.year))
    for i in range(len(train) - min_train_size - horizon):
        '''
        training window 
        '''
        df_train = df[df.year.isin(train[:min_train_size+i])].copy().reset_index(drop=True)
        mean = df_train[feats_to_use].mean(axis=0)
        df_train[feats_to_use] = df_train[feats_to_use].fillna(mean)   
        X_train = df_train[feats_to_use].apply(normalize).values
        y_train = df_train.loc[:,target]
        '''
        validation window 
        '''
        df_val = df[df.year.isin(train[min_train_size+i:min_train_size+i+horizon])].copy().reset_index(drop=True)
        mean = df_val[feats_to_use].mean(axis=0)
        df_val[feats_to_use] = df_val[feats_to_use].fillna(mean)  
        X_val = df_val[feats_to_use].apply(normalize).values
        y_val = df_val.loc[:,target]
        '''
        test window 
        '''
        df_test = df[df.year.isin(train[min_train_size+i+horizon:min_train_size+i+horizon+1])].copy().reset_index(drop=True)
        mean = df_test[feats_to_use].mean(axis=0)
        df_test[feats_to_use] = df_test[feats_to_use].fillna(mean)  
        X_test = df_test[feats_to_use].apply(normalize).values
        y_test = df_test.loc[:,target]
        
        yield X_train,y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test


def feat_imp(model):
    '''
    feature importance
    '''    
    cv = data_sliding_window(df = df, min_train_size = 20, horizon =1)
    feat_imp = pd.DataFrame(index=feats_to_use)
    i = 0 
    for X_train,y_train, X_val,y_val,X_test,y_test in cv:
        model.fit(X_train,y_train)
        perm = PermutationImportance(model, scoring ='r2').fit(X_train,y_train)
        exp = eli5.explain_weights_df(perm,feature_names = feats_to_use).set_index('feature')
        feat_imp[i] = exp['weight']
        i += 1
    
    feat_imp['feature_importance'] = feat_imp.mean(axis=1)
    return pd.DataFrame(feat_imp.feature_importance)

        
def feat_imp_plot(data,title):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,14))
    data['feature_importance'].sort_values(ascending=True).plot(kind='barh',x = 'feature_importance')
    plt.title(title)
    plt.autoscale(enable=True, axis='x', tight=False)
    plt.show()

def feat_imp_20(data,title):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    data['feature_importance'].sort_values(ascending=True).iloc[59:79].plot(kind='barh',x = 'feature_importance')
    plt.title(title)
    plt.autoscale(enable=True, axis='x', tight=False)
    plt.show()
    
def model_performance(model):
    '''
    performance.
    '''
    cv = sliding_window(df = df, min_train_size = 19, horizon =1)
    val_true = []
    val_pred = []
    test_true = []
    test_pred = []
    feat_imp = pd.DataFrame(index=feats_to_use)
    i = 0 
    for X_train,y_train, X_val,y_val,X_test,y_test in cv:
        model.fit(X_train,y_train)
        val = model.predict(X_val)
        pred = model.predict(X_test)
        val_true.append(y_val)
        val_pred.append(val)
        test_true.append(y_test)
        test_pred.append(pred)
        perm = PermutationImportance(model).fit(X_train,y_train)
        exp = eli5.explain_weights_df(perm,feature_names = feats_to_use).set_index('feature')
        feat_imp[i] = exp['weight']
        i += 1
    
    feat_imp['feature_importance'] = feat_imp.mean(axis=1)
    feat_result = pd.DataFrame(feat_imp.feature_importance)
    R2_val = R2(np.concatenate(val_true),np.concatenate(val_pred))
    R2_test = R2(np.concatenate(test_true),np.concatenate(test_pred))
    return R2_val,R2_test, feat_result

def long_short(model):
    
    long_ret_l = []
    short_ret_l = []
    time=[]

    for i in range(len(train) - min_train_size - horizon):
        df_train =df[df.year.isin(train[:min_train_size+i])].copy().reset_index(drop=True)
        mean = df_train[feats_to_use].mean(axis=0)
        df_train[feats_to_use] = df_train[feats_to_use].fillna(mean) 
        X_train = df_train[feats_to_use].apply(normalize).values
        
        df_test = df[df.year.isin(train[min_train_size+i+horizon:min_train_size+i+horizon+1])].copy().reset_index(drop=True)
        mean = df_test[feats_to_use].mean(axis=0)
        df_test[feats_to_use] = df_test[feats_to_use].fillna(mean)  
        X_test = df_test[feats_to_use].apply(normalize).values

        model.fit(X_train,df_train[target])
        y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
        df_test['est_y'] = y_pred
        time_gr_test = df_test.groupby(['year','month'])

        cum_long_ret = 1
        cum_short_ret = 1
        for t in list(time_gr_test.nunique().index):
            time.append(t)
            test = time_gr_test.get_group(t)
            test = test.sort_values('est_y', ascending=False)
            long_ret = np.mean(test[target].head(int(test.shape[0]/10)))
            long_ret_l.append(long_ret)
            cum_long_ret = cum_long_ret*(1+long_ret)
            short_ret = np.mean(test[target].tail(int(test.shape[0]/10)))
            short_ret_l.append(short_ret)
            cum_short_ret = cum_short_ret*(1+short_ret)
    
    date = [datetime.date(t[0],t[1],1).strftime('%m/%Y') for t in time]
    cum_long = np.cumsum(long_ret_l)
    cum_short = np.cumsum(short_ret_l)
    return date, cum_long, cum_short

# define NN model
np.random.seed(12345)

class MLPRegressor_O(MLPRegressor):
    def _init_coef(self, fan_in, fan_out):
        if self.activation == 'logistic':
            init_bound = np.sqrt(2. / (fan_in + fan_out))
        elif self.activation in ('identity', 'tanh', 'relu'): 
            init_bound = np.sqrt(6. / (fan_in + fan_out))
        else:
            raise ValueError("Unknown activation function %s" %self.activation)
        coef_init = np.random.uniform(-0.01,0.01,(fan_in,fan_out)) 
        intercept_init = np.random.uniform(-0.01,0.01,fan_out) 
        return coef_init, intercept_init

# NN1~5 model

# LGB model
class LGB_model():
    def __init__(self, num_leaves=25, feature_fraction=0.6, bagging_fraction=0.6):
        self.lgb_params = {'task': 'train','boosting_type': 'gbdt','objective': 'regression','metric': {'l2'},'learning_rate': 0.01,'bagging_freq': 5,'num_thread':4,'verbose': 0}
        self.lgb_params['feature_fraction'] = feature_fraction
        self.lgb_params['bagging_fraction'] = bagging_fraction
        self.lgb_params['num_leaves'] = num_leaves
        self.bestmodel=None
    def fit(self, train, y):
        X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(train, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=343)
        lgtrain = lgb.Dataset(X_train, y_train)
        lgval = lgb.Dataset(X_val, y_val, reference=lgtrain)
        self.bestmodel = lgb.train(self.lgb_params,lgtrain,num_boost_round=100,valid_sets=lgval,verbose_eval=False,early_stopping_rounds=5)
    def predict(self, test):
        return self.bestmodel.predict(test, num_iteration=self.bestmodel.best_iteration)
    def feature_importance(self, imptype="gain"):
        return self.bestmodel.feature_importance(importance_type=imptype)

# parameters and model
num_leaf = 70
feature_fraction = 0.6
bagging_fraction = 0.7

LGB_model = LGB_model(num_leaves=num_leaf, feature_fraction=feature_fraction, bagging_fraction=bagging_fraction)

time=[]

feat_imp = pd.DataFrame(index=feats_to_use)

for i in range(len(train) - min_train_size - horizon):
    df_train =df[df.year.isin(train[:min_train_size+i])].copy().reset_index(drop=True)
    mean = df_train[feats_to_use].mean(axis=0)
    df_train[feats_to_use] = df_train[feats_to_use].fillna(mean)
    X_train = df_train[feats_to_use].apply(normalize).values
    
    df_val = df[df.year.isin(train[min_train_size+i:min_train_size+i+horizon])].copy().reset_index(drop=True)
    mean = df_val[feats_to_use].mean(axis=0)
    df_val[feats_to_use] = df_val[feats_to_use].fillna(mean)
    X_val = df_val[feats_to_use].apply(normalize).values
    
    df_test = df[df.year.isin(train[min_train_size+i+horizon:min_train_size+i+horizon+1])].copy().reset_index(drop=True)
    mean = df_test[feats_to_use].mean(axis=0)
    df_test[feats_to_use] = df_test[feats_to_use].fillna(mean) 
    X_test = df_test[feats_to_use].apply(normalize).values

    LGB_model.fit(X_train,df_train[target])
    y_val = LGB_model.predict(X_val)
    y_pred = LGB_model.predict(X_test)
    y_val_true = df_val[target]
    y_pred_true = df_test[target]
    LGB_val.append(y_val)
    LGB_val_true.append(y_val_true)
    LGB_test.append(y_pred)
    LGB_test_true.append(y_pred_true)
    
    # feature importance 
    exp = pd.DataFrame(LGB_model.feature_importance(),index=feats_to_use)
    
    feat_imp[i] = exp

    # Long-short portfolio based on LGB model
    df_test['est_y'] = y_pred
    time_gr_test = df_test.groupby(['year','month'])

    cum_long_ret = 1
    cum_short_ret = 1
    for t in list(time_gr_test.nunique().index):
        time.append(t)
        test = time_gr_test.get_group(t)
        test = test.sort_values('est_y', ascending=False)
        long_ret = np.mean(test[target].head(int(test.shape[0]/10)))
        long_ret_l.append(long_ret)
        cum_long_ret = cum_long_ret*(1+long_ret)
        short_ret = np.mean(test[target].tail(int(test.shape[0]/10)))
        short_ret_l.append(short_ret)
        cum_short_ret = cum_short_ret*(1+short_ret)
    

LGB_date = [datetime.date(t[0],t[1],1).strftime('%m/%Y') for t in time]
LGB_cum_long = np.cumsum(long_ret_l)
LGB_cum_short = np.cumsum(short_ret_l)


print(R2(np.concatenate(LGB_val_true),np.concatenate(LGB_val)))
print(R2(np.concatenate(LGB_test_true),np.concatenate(LGB_test)))
